===Noun phrase===
'''Afro-pessimism'''

# The notion concocted ideology that the future of [[Africa]] must continually be projected to the world as bleak by Western controlled media for the purpose of social imbalance, political manipulation and geopolitical control of Africas abundant resources.  Inciting constant conflict, creating divisions and supporting corrupt government is a means to the end of causing a multitude of problems on the continent, to be faced by the aspiring, yet ill-prepared African people. Pessimism, faithlessness and negative thought automates a self-perpetuating, self defeating psychology and nurtures a culture of dependence and self-destruction. External systems of remote neocolonial economic control transcend the political fallacy of African independence. What is believed is known to be created. A negative philosophy of life practically insures negative choices in life.  A choice, in turn, manifests itself as ones individual or social history.